request.description:
‚ö†Ô∏è IMPORTANT: Postman doesn't fully support Socket.IO handshake/events.

‚úÖ Use the included test page:
- Open: {{base_url}}/websocket-test.html

Socket.IO Endpoint:
- URL: http://localhost:3001
- Namespace: /classroom
- Path: /socket.io (default)

Client connect example:
io('http://localhost:3001/classroom', { auth: { token: STUDENT_JWT } })

üîê Authentication:
- socket.handshake.auth.token = JWT

üì° CORE EVENTS (LOCKED)

Teacher/Admin ‚Üí Server:
- CREATE_SESSION { classId, topic }
- LAUNCH_POLL { sessionId, question, options[] }
- END_SESSION { sessionId } ‚Üí Ends session voluntarily

Server ‚Üí Teacher/Admin:
- SESSION_CREATED { sessionId }
- CONFUSION_UPDATE { totalSignals, confusedPercentage }
- ENGAGEMENT_UPDATE { avgEngagement, lowEngagementCount }
- POLL_RESULTS { results, totalResponses }
- SESSION_ENDED_CONFIRM { sessionId }
- SESSION_STATS { totalStudents }

Student ‚Üí Server:
- JOIN_SESSION { sessionId }
- CONFUSION_SIGNAL { level: 1 }
- ENGAGEMENT_SIGNAL { idleTime, scrollSpeed, tabFocus }
- POLL_RESPONSE { pollId, optionIndex }
- LEAVE_SESSION { sessionId } ‚Üí Leaves session voluntarily

Server ‚Üí Student:
- JOINED_SESSION { sessionId, anonymousId }
- POLL_LAUNCHED { pollId, question, options[] }
- SESSION_ENDED { sessionId, message }
- LEFT_SESSION { sessionId, message }

Steps to test (quick):
1) Login TEACHER in Postman ‚Üí copy token
2) Open websocket-test.html in Tab A (Teacher mode), paste token, Connect
3) Enter classId + topic ‚Üí CREATE_SESSION ‚Üí copy sessionId
4) Login STUDENT in Postman ‚Üí copy token
5) Open websocket-test.html in Tab B/C (Student mode), paste token, Connect
6) Paste sessionId ‚Üí JOIN_SESSION ‚Üí click CONFUSION_SIGNAL / ENGAGEMENT_SIGNAL
7) Back in teacher tab, observe CONFUSION_UPDATE / ENGAGEMENT_UPDATE
8) Teacher launches poll ‚Üí students respond ‚Üí teacher receives POLL_RESULTS
9) Student can LEAVE_SESSION or Teacher can END_SESSION

Full guide: WEBSOCKET_TESTING_GUIDE.md
